-blogging-from-markdown","score":5,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"\u003cp\u003eWith the addition of ActivityPub support (through \u003ca href=\"https://git.fabiomanganiello.com/pubby\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ePubby\u003c/a\u003e), Madblog is now a fully federated blogging platform with zero database and zero JavaScript that can run from any folder with Markdown files.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"With the addition of ActivityPub support (through [Pubby](https://git.fabiomanganiello.com/pubby)), Madblog is now a fully federated blogging platform with zero database and zero JavaScript that can run from any folder with Markdown files.","submitter_user":"blacklight","user_is_author":true,"tags":["networking","python","web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/9nzeu7","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/9nzeu7/madblog_turn_markdown_folder_into"},{"short_id":"cpqm9i","created_at":"2026-03-10T07:13:03.000-05:00","title":"Too Much Color","url":"https://www.keithcirkel.co.uk/too-much-color/","score":10,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"polywolf","user_is_author":false,"tags":["graphics","web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cpqm9i","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cpqm9i/too_much_color"},{"short_id":"gh0mwq","created_at":"2026-03-10T06:51:21.000-05:00","title":"nominal types in webassembly","url":"https://wingolog.org/archives/2026/03/10/nominal-types-in-webassembly","score":11,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"flockofbirbs","user_is_author":false,"tags":["wasm"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gh0mwq","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gh0mwq/nominal_types_webassembly"},{"short_id":"izdkzi","created_at":"2026-03-10T06:38:07.000-05:00","title":"TCXO failure analysis","url":"https://serd.es/2026/03/06/TCXO-failure-analysis.html","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"gerikson","user_is_author":false,"tags":["hardware"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/izdkzi","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/izdkzi/tcxo_failure_analysis"},{"short_id":"l4bpve","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:17:02.000-05:00","title":"AI, Decomputing and the Interregnum","url":"https://zenodo.org/records/18908530/files/ai_decomputing_interregnum_danmcquillan.pdf","score":1,"flags":1,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eThis paper treats AI as diagnostic for the deeper changes taking place in the existing order of things. It uses AI's alignment with both the political economy and with the dualisms that underpin it, including race, gender and anthropocentrism, to highlight the nihilistic character of the current restructuring. AI's scaling and accelerationism are taken as examples of the wider tactics being invoked by hegemonic power to maintain control under changing conditions. From this perspective, the massive build-out of data centres isn't simply a seizure of energy resources but a manifestation of an aggressive and misogynist technopolitics. The paper argues that a liberal push for digital sovereignty doesn't interrupt these dynamics but plays into the hands of emerging technofascism. It proposes instead the prefigurative tactic of 'decomputing', which draws on degrowth, deautomatisation and a convivial approach to technology. It explores decomputing as a means to mitigate both material and relational harms and as a decisive turn towards infrastructuring the common good. The paper concludes that AI is the contradiction that reveals many others, not least the gap between claims to legitimacy and the actuality of destructive violence, and proposes an alternative technopolitics of reciprocity that prioritises care and sustainability.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"This paper treats AI as diagnostic for the deeper changes taking place in the existing order of things. It uses AI's alignment with both the political economy and with the dualisms that underpin it, including race, gender and anthropocentrism, to highlight the nihilistic character of the current restructuring. AI's scaling and accelerationism are taken as examples of the wider tactics being invoked by hegemonic power to maintain control under changing conditions. From this perspective, the massive build-out of data centres isn't simply a seizure of energy resources but a manifestation of an aggressive and misogynist technopolitics. The paper argues that a liberal push for digital sovereignty doesn't interrupt these dynamics but plays into the hands of emerging technofascism. It proposes instead the prefigurative tactic of 'decomputing', which draws on degrowth, deautomatisation and a convivial approach to technology. It explores decomputing as a means to mitigate both material and relational harms and as a decisive turn towards infrastructuring the common good. The paper concludes that AI is the contradiction that reveals many others, not least the gap between claims to legitimacy and the actuality of destructive violence, and proposes an alternative technopolitics of reciprocity that prioritises care and sustainability.","submitter_user":"smyds","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai","pdf","philosophy"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/l4bpve","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/l4bpve/ai_decomputing_interregnum"},{"short_id":"vkxmwj","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:07:13.000-05:00","title":"Redox OS has adopted a Certificate of Origin policy and a strict no-LLM policy","url":"https://gitlab.redox-os.org/redox-os/redox/-/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md","score":22,"flags":0,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"linkdd","user_is_author":false,"tags":["osdev","rust"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vkxmwj","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vkxmwj/redox_os_has_adopted_certificate_origin"},{"short_id":"qfkqct","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:06:13.000-05:00","title":"Working to Decentralize FedCM","url":"https://atproto.com/blog/working-to-